---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

export const prerender = true;
---

<Base
  title="Privacy"
  description="What I collect when you subscribe to the Pyrrhic Stars devlog."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-chrome-400 font-medium">
        Legal
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-text-primary">
        Privacy notice.
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-text-secondary">
      <p>
        This page explains what I collect when you sign up for the Pyrrhic Stars
        devlog newsletter. It is intentionally short.
      </p>

      <h2>What I collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Email address</strong>: provided by you when you submit
          the subscribe form. Used solely to send the weekly devlog.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Subscription source</strong>: the page you signed up
          from (e.g. <code>home</code>). Helps me understand which copy is
          working.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Subscription timestamp</strong>: when you signed up.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I do not collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          I do <strong>not</strong> store IP addresses in the database. Rate
          limiting happens in memory only and is discarded between deployments.
        </li>
        <li>
          I do <strong>not</strong> use third-party tracking, analytics, or
          advertising cookies on this site.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to unsubscribe</h2>
      <p>
        Every devlog email contains an unsubscribe link. Click it and you are
        removed from the list. I do not require a login to unsubscribe.
      </p>

      <h2>Where the data is stored</h2>
      <p>
        Email addresses are stored in a Postgres database hosted on the same
        infrastructure that runs the game. I do not share the list with third
        parties.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions, open a thread in the
        <a href="/#hero">Discord</a> or open an issue on the public repository.
      </p>

      <p class="text-text-muted text-sm">
        Last updated: 2026-06-02.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
